'''Kaan Ayhan''' (born 10 November 1994) is a professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)|defender]] for [[Süper Lig]] club [[Galatasaray S.K. (football)|Galatasaray]]. Born in Germany, he plays for the [[Turkey national football team|Turkey national team]].

==Club career==
=== Schalke 04 ===
Ayhan joined [[FC Schalke 04|Schalke 04]]'s youth academy when he was four years old.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.schalke04.de/de/profis/team/kader/verteidiger/kaan-ayhan/page/1838-1179-1838--.html?h=spieler/17294|publisher=Schalke 04|title=Kaan Ayhan|access-date=7 October 2013|language=de|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131017122800/http://www.schalke04.de/de/profis/team/kader/verteidiger/kaan-ayhan/page/1838-1179-1838--.html?h=spieler%2F17294|archive-date=17 October 2013}}</ref> On 18 January 2012, he signed a professional contract with Schalke 04 that would last until 30 June 2015.<ref>{{cite web|title=Schalke-Talent Kaan Ayhan erhält Profi-Vertrag|url=https://www.derwesten.de/sport/fussball/s04/schalke-talent-kaan-ayhan-erhaelt-profi-vertrag-id6259553.html|publisher=Der Westen|date=18 January 2012|access-date=7 October 2013|language=de|archive-date=20 January 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120120213425/https://www.derwesten.de/sport/fussball/s04/schalke-talent-kaan-ayhan-erhaelt-profi-vertrag-id6259553.html|url-status=dead}}</ref> Ayhan was assigned a number 24 shirt.<ref>{{cite web|title=Kaan Ayhan ist der dienstälteste Knappe|url=http://www.schalke04.de/de/aktuell/news/130705_ayhan/page/1924--10-213--213.html|publisher=Schalke 04|date=5 July 2013|access-date=4 October 2013|language=de|archive-date=7 October 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131007161122/http://www.schalke04.de/de/aktuell/news/130705_ayhan/page/1924--10-213--213.html|url-status=dead}}</ref> Ayhan made his debut against [[FC Augsburg]] in a 4–1 win on 5 October 2013, coming on as a substitute for [[Ádám Szalai]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Schalke 4 Augsburg 1|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2013/10/05/germany/bundesliga/fc-schalke-04/fc-augsburg/1487087/|work=Soccerway|date=5 October 2013|access-date=7 October 2013|archive-date=24 September 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130924095955/https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2013/10/05/germany/bundesliga/fc-schalke-04/fc-augsburg/1487087/|url-status=live}}</ref> On 3 May 2014, Ayhan scored his first Bundesliga goal in the 13th minute of a 2–0 victory at [[SC Freiburg]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Job almost done for Schalke|url=http://www.bundesliga.com/en/liga/news/2013/0000293200.php|publisher=Bundesliga|date=3 May 2014|access-date=4 May 2014|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140504230540/http://www.bundesliga.com/en/liga/news/2013/0000293200.php|archive-date=4 May 2014}}</ref>

In January 2016, Ayhan joined [[Eintracht Frankfurt]] on loan from Schalke for the second half of the season.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Walsh|first1=Jonathan|title=Kaan Ayhan swaps Schalke for Frankfurt|url=http://www.vavel.com/en/international-football/germany-bundesliga/585784-kaan-ayhan-swaps-schalke-for-frankfurt.html|website=Vavel|access-date=3 January 2016|archive-date=4 March 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304041532/http://www.vavel.com/en/international-football/germany-bundesliga/585784-kaan-ayhan-swaps-schalke-for-frankfurt.html|url-status=live}}</ref> Frankfurt secured the option of signing him permanently, however, the fixed transfer fee was reported as being too high for a permanent signing to be likely.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Lieto|first1=Toni|title=Ayhans Ziel: Mit Spielpraxis zurück zum FC Schalke|url=https://www.kicker.de/ayhans-ziel_mit-spielpraxis-zurueck-zum-fc-schalke-642176/artikel|access-date=3 January 2016|work=Kicker Online|date=3 January 2015|language=de|archive-date=7 January 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160107072523/http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/bundesliga/vereine/642176/artikel_ayhans-ziel_mit-spielpraxis-zurueck-zum-fc-schalke.html|url-status=live}}</ref>

=== Fortuna Düsseldorf ===
On 31 August 2016, Ayhan left [[Schalke 04]] after 17 years at the club to join [[2. Bundesliga]] side [[Fortuna Düsseldorf]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.schalke04.de/en/news/160831_ayhanf95/page/2442--86-86-.html|title=Ayhan moves to Fortuna Düsseldorf|publisher=Schalke 04|date=31 August 2016|access-date=31 August 2016|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160911193029/http://www.schalke04.de/en/news/160831_ayhanf95/page/2442--86-86-.html|archive-date=11 September 2016}}</ref>

On 13 May 2017 Ayhan scored the third goal in a 3-2 for win over [[1. FC Nürnberg]], securing the [[2017–18 2. Bundesliga]] title for Fortuna Düsseldorf.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://rp-online.de/sport/fussball/fortuna/fortuna-duesseldorf-kaan-ayhan-sucht-sein-trikot-und-findet-es-bei-bibiana-steinhaus_aid-22633437|title=Fortuna Düsseldorf: Kaan Ayhan sucht sein Trikot – und findet es bei Bibiana Steinhaus|first=Falk|last=Janning|website=rp-online.de|date=14 May 2018|access-date=19 May 2018|archive-date=19 May 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180519205022/https://rp-online.de/sport/fussball/fortuna/fortuna-duesseldorf-kaan-ayhan-sucht-sein-trikot-und-findet-es-bei-bibiana-steinhaus_aid-22633437|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2018/05/13/germany/2-bundesliga/1-fc-nurnberg/dusseldorfer-tus-fortuna-1895-ev/2480871/|title=Nürnberg vs. Fortuna Düsseldorf - 13 May 2018 - Soccerway|website=int.soccerway.com|access-date=19 May 2018|archive-date=19 May 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180519231358/https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2018/05/13/germany/2-bundesliga/1-fc-nurnberg/dusseldorfer-tus-fortuna-1895-ev/2480871/|url-status=live}}</ref>

=== Sassuolo ===
On 16 August 2020, Ayhan joined [[Serie A]] club [[U.S. Sassuolo Calcio|Sassuolo]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sassuolocalcio.it/in-evidenza/calciomercato-dal-fortuna-dusseldorf-arriva-kaan-ayhan/|title=Calciomercato: dal Fortuna Düsseldorf arriva Kaan Ayhan|website=U.S. Sassuolo Calcio|language=it|access-date=26 April 2023|archive-date=26 April 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230426150728/https://www.sassuolocalcio.it/in-evidenza/calciomercato-dal-fortuna-dusseldorf-arriva-kaan-ayhan/|url-status=live}}</ref>

=== Galatasaray ===
On 28 January 2023, [[Galatasaray S.K. (football)|Galatasaray]] announced the official negotiations for the temporary transfer of Kaan Ayhan from [[U.S. Sassuolo Calcio|Sassuolo]] till the end of the season.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.galatasaray.org/haber/kulup/kaan-ayhanin-gecici-transferi-hakkinda/52645|title=Kaan Ayhan'ın geçici transferi hakkında|publisher=Galatasaray S.K.|date=28 January 2023|access-date=29 January 2023|archive-date=28 January 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230128224605/https://www.galatasaray.org/haber/kulup/kaan-ayhanin-gecici-transferi-hakkinda/52645|url-status=live}}</ref> On 30 January 2023, the transfer was confirmed by Sassuolo as an initial loan with an obligation to buy.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=U.S. Sassuolo Calcio|url=https://www.sassuolocalcio.it/in-evidenza/calciomercato-kaan-ayhan-ceduto-al-galatasaray/|title=CALCIOMERCATO: KAAN AYHAN CEDUTO AL GALATASARAY|date=30 January 2023|access-date=30 January 2023|language=it|archive-date=30 January 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230130170936/https://www.sassuolocalcio.it/in-evidenza/calciomercato-kaan-ayhan-ceduto-al-galatasaray/|url-status=dead}}</ref>

Ayhan became a champion in the [[Süper Lig]] in the [[2022–23 Süper Lig|2022–23]] season with the [[Galatasaray S.K. (football)|Galatasaray]] team. Defeating [[MKE Ankaragücü|Ankaragücü]] 4–1 away in the match played in the 36th week on 30 May 2023, Galatasaray secured the lead with 2 weeks before the end and won the 23rd championship in its history.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/65761517|title=Turkish Super Lig: Galatasaray win title for 23rd time after beating Ankaragucu 4-1|publisher=BBC Sport|date=May 30, 2023|access-date=May 31, 2023|archive-date=2 June 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230602093025/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/65761517|url-status=live}}</ref>

Following the season, it was announced that Galatasaray had triggered the buy option on Ayhan's loan deal at the cost of €2.8 million.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.galatasaray.org/haber/gs-sportif-a-s/profesyonel-futbolcu-kaan-ayhanin-transferi-hakkinda/53489|title=Profesyonel Futbolcu Kaan Ayhan'ın Transferi Hakkında|publisher=Galatasaray S.K.|date=1 July 2023|access-date=1 July 2023|archive-date=1 July 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230701151143/https://www.galatasaray.org/haber/gs-sportif-a-s/profesyonel-futbolcu-kaan-ayhanin-transferi-hakkinda/53489|url-status=live}}</ref>

==International career==
A Turkish-German, Ayhan has been [[cap (sport)|capped]] by both Germany and Turkey junior national teams. In October 2013, Ayhan was selected for the [[Turkey national under-21 football team|Turkey under-21]] squad.<ref>{{cite web | title = Ümit Milli Takım'ın Yunanistan ve Polonya maçları aday kadrosu belli oldu | url = http://www.tff.org/default.aspx?pageID=284&ftxtID=19110 | publisher = TFF | date = 5 October 2013 | access-date = 7 October 2013 | language = tr | archive-date = 16 September 2018 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20180916022746/http://www.tff.org/default.aspx?pageID=284&ftxtID=19110 | url-status = live }}</ref> He was called up by manager [[Fatih Terim]] for [[Turkey national football team|Turkey]]'s friendly match against [[Russia national football team|Russia]] on 31 August 2016, and subsequent [[2018 FIFA World Cup qualification – UEFA Group I|World Cup 2018 qualifier]] against [[Croatia national football team|Croatia]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Fatih Terim'den sürpriz kadro!|url=http://spor.haber7.com/milli-takim/haber/2095678-fatih-terimden-surpriz-kadro|access-date=29 August 2016|publisher=spor.haber7.com|date=26 August 2016|archive-date=6 November 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201106111843/https://spor.haber7.com/milli-takim/haber/2095678-fatih-terimden-surpriz-kadro|url-status=live}}</ref> Kaan Ayhan gave his debut for the Turkey national football team on 31 August 2016 in a friendly against Russia.<ref>{{cite web |title=Turkey vs. Russia |url=http://www.espnfc.us/match?gameId=464419 |access-date=1 September 2016 |archive-date=4 September 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160904124128/http://www.espnfc.us/match?gameId=464419 |url-status=live }}</ref>

He was named in Turkey's 26-man squad for [[UEFA Euro 2024]].<ref>{{cite news |date=7 June 2024 |title=A Millî Takımımızın EURO 2024 Aday Kadrosu Açıklandı |trans-title=EURO 2024 Candidate Squad of Our National Team Announced |url=https://www.tff.org/default.aspx?pageID=202&ftxtID=44561 |language=tr |publisher=[[Turkish Football Federation]] |access-date=18 June 2024 |archive-date=7 June 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240607205837/https://tff.org/default.aspx?pageID=202&ftxtID=44561 |url-status=live }}</ref>

